Reconstruction of Stonehenge (c. 3200–1500 BCE), Prehistoric/Neolithic. Massive sarsen and bluestone megaliths in post-and-lintel form huge uprights in a circle and inner horseshoe with lintels (trilithons), smaller inner rings. Rough, weathered stone with simple tool marks. Precise symmetry and solar alignment on open grassland. No metal or writing, raw geometry. Ceremonial site for ritual, burial, and seasonal gatherings by early farming communities
